{"blocks":[{"key":"bu33k","text":"Reagents Needed:
Liquid Nitrogen
CTAB Extraction Buffer + PVP
CTAB Precipitation Buffer (pH=7.2-7.6)
24:1 Chloroform: Isoamyl alcohol
100% Isopropanol (ice cold)
70% Ethanol (ice cold)
100% Ethanol (ice cold)
3M Sodium Acetate (pH=5.2)","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":0,"length":16}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"e86h0","text":"5M NaCl
UltraPure water or TE buffer
Proteinase K 20mg/mL
RNase A 10 mg/mL","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"e4rpv","text":"
Instruments/Materials Needed:
Bead beating tubes
0.5 mm Glass beads
Dewar for Liquid Nitrogen
Water bath or heat block set to 70° C
1.5mL Microcentrifuge tubes
2.0mL Microcentrifuge tubes
15mL Centrifuge tubes
Fridge and Freezer (4° C and -20° C)
Pipettes
Refrigerated Microcentrifuge
Fungal samples, 0.03g minimum

status.info: We use this protocol and it's working

steps.section: Preparing Yeast from liquid culture for DNA extraction
steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"enou0","text":"Grow fungi in preferred media type till fungi are in mid-exponential phase","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

steps.section: Preparing Yeast from liquid culture for DNA extraction
steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"b2un3","text":"Centrifuge fungal samples at 10,000x g for 1 minute and wash with water 3 times, centrifuging in between, then obtain as tight of a fungal pellet as possible and remove all liquid from the tube.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

steps.section: Preparing Yeast from solid culture for DNA extraction
steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"4bq16","text":"Grow fungi on preferred media type till fungi grows to its maximum on the plate","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

steps.section: Preparing Yeast from solid culture for DNA extraction
steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"65r2l","text":"Place 800µL of water in a 1.5mL tube and weigh recording the weight","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

steps.section: Preparing Yeast from solid culture for DNA extraction
steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"8qdn1","text":"Scrape 0.03g of fungus off the plate and place into the tube, avoiding agar","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

steps.section: Preparing Yeast from solid culture for DNA extraction
steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"b5uu","text":"Centrifuge at 10,000x for 1 minute to obtain a fungal pellet and remove all water ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

steps.section: Lysing Filamentous fungi
steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"crk38","text":"Grab as many mortar and pestles as necessary for the number of samples you have (or wash one out thoroughly with 70% ethanol between samples)","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

steps.section: Lysing Filamentous fungi
steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"9j4p3","text":"Obtain liquid nitrogen placed in Dewar","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

steps.section: Lysing Filamentous fungi
steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"9ghra","text":"Place tubes with processed fungi in a small container and pour liquid nitrogen over the tubes until the fungi pellets are frozen completely","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

steps.section: Lysing Filamentous fungi
steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"79ojc","text":"With tube lids closed, tap the lids against the table to dislodge the pellet from the tube","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

steps.section: Lysing Filamentous fungi
steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"3umdc","text":"Put the frozen fungal pellet into the mortar and pour additional sterile Liquid nitrogen over the pellet","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

steps.section: Lysing Filamentous fungi
steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"96i8k","text":"Carefully grind the fungus being sure not to launch it out of the mortar, grind till the fungus is a powder, adding more liquid nitrogen if the fungus gets too liquidy","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

steps.section: Lysing Filamentous fungi
steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"a8u1","text":"Scrape ground up fungus out of the mortar and place in a fresh 1.5mL tube, place sample in -80° C freezer until ready for DNA extraction.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

steps.section: DNA extraction Protocol (from cell growth to final DNA product):
steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"9j2t6","text":"Grow fungi in preferred media type till fungi are in mid-exponential phase (3-7 days)","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

steps.section: DNA extraction Protocol (from cell growth to final DNA product):
steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"bjpnt","text":"Pipette 1 mL of fungus into a 1.5 mL tube","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

steps.section: DNA extraction Protocol (from cell growth to final DNA product):
steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"20v4l","text":"Centrifuge fungal samples at 10,000x g for 1 minute","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

steps.section: DNA extraction Protocol (from cell growth to final DNA product):
steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"5m02u","text":"Wash with 1 mL of ddH2O 3 times, centrifuging in between, then obtain as tight of a fungal pellet as possible and remove all liquid from the tube","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

steps.section: DNA extraction Protocol (from cell growth to final DNA product):
steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"33lfc","text":"Take your 1.5 mL tube of washed cell pellet and place in liquid nitrogen to flash freeze and place tubes in -80 freezer till you’re ready to extract DNA","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

steps.section: DNA extraction Protocol (from cell growth to final DNA product):
steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"uher","text":"Turn on water bath/heat block to 70° C","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

steps.section: DNA extraction Protocol (from cell growth to final DNA product):
steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"6f5f8","text":"Determine the number of samples you will be processing, multiply that number by 750 µL to determine the amount of CTAB Extraction buffer you will need (700 µL per sample) and aliquot that out into a 15 mL centrifuge tube","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

steps.section: DNA extraction Protocol (from cell growth to final DNA product):
steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"fuetu","text":"Add 1% w/v PVP (.01g/mL) and 1% v/v 20mg/mL Proteinase K (5µL/500µL) to your aliquoted CTAB Extraction buffer","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

steps.section: DNA extraction Protocol (from cell growth to final DNA product):
steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"1dqdk","text":"Grab as many bead beating tubes as you have samples","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

steps.section: DNA extraction Protocol (from cell growth to final DNA product):
steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"vi8p","text":"Pour ~300uL of glass beads into tubes and label tubes accordingly","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

steps.section: DNA extraction Protocol (from cell growth to final DNA product):
steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"ag92d","text":"Remove tubes of frozen fungus from the freezer","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

steps.section: DNA extraction Protocol (from cell growth to final DNA product):
steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"2jfhq","text":"Dislodge pellet from bottom of tube by pipetting 700 µL of the complete CTAB Extraction buffer into each frozen sample tube","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

steps.section: DNA extraction Protocol (from cell growth to final DNA product):
steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"c0t0a","text":"Transfer sample in CTAB Extraction buffer to Bead beating tube","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

steps.section: DNA extraction Protocol (from cell growth to final DNA product):
steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"chcgu","text":"Put tubes in 70 °C water bath or heat block for 5 minutes, then bead beat for 5 minutes; repeat 2 more times (30 mins total) (change temperature of heat block/water bath to 37° C after this step, unless you have a 37° C incubator)","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

steps.section: DNA extraction Protocol (from cell growth to final DNA product):
steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"blmvc","text":"Confirm cells have lysed via microscopy, 5 µL of sample onto a microscope slide. If cells have not lysed, bead beat for additional 2-5 minutes.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

steps.section: DNA extraction Protocol (from cell growth to final DNA product):
steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"7tivc","text":"Remove tubes from the water bath/heat block and transfer as much liquid as possible into a new 2 mL microcentrifuge tube, avoiding the glass beads","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

steps.section: DNA extraction Protocol (from cell growth to final DNA product):
steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"se57","text":"Add 1x the volume of 24:1 Chloroform: Isoamyl to the tubes, invert tubes to mix and then centrifuge tubes at 10,000x g for 5 minutes","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

steps.section: DNA extraction Protocol (from cell growth to final DNA product):
steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"1m3jp","text":"Carefully remove tubes from centrifuge, collect upper layer only, and transfer the upper layer into a new 2 mL microcentrifuge tube","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

steps.section: DNA extraction Protocol (from cell growth to final DNA product):
steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"a8k44","text":"Add 2 volumes of CTAB Precipitation buffer to the tubes and mix by inverting for 2 minutes","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

steps.section: DNA extraction Protocol (from cell growth to final DNA product):
steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"4l12s","text":"Centrifuge tubes at 13,000x g for 15 minutes","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

steps.section: DNA extraction Protocol (from cell growth to final DNA product):
steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"5ghca","text":"Remove supernatant, being sure to leave the pellet behind in the tube","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

steps.section: DNA extraction Protocol (from cell growth to final DNA product):
steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"b41i0","text":"Re-suspend pellet in 350 µL of 5M NaCl","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

steps.section: DNA extraction Protocol (from cell growth to final DNA product):
steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"677j5","text":"Add 2µL of 10 mg/mL RNase A to tubes and place tubes at 37° C for 30 minutes","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

steps.section: DNA extraction Protocol (from cell growth to final DNA product):
steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"8jc47","text":"Remove tubes from 37° C and add one volume of 24:1 Chloroform: Isoamyl; mix thoroughly by inverting","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

steps.section: DNA extraction Protocol (from cell growth to final DNA product):
steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"dkor3","text":"Centrifuge tubes at 10,000x g for 5 minutes","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

steps.section: DNA extraction Protocol (from cell growth to final DNA product):
steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"as991","text":"Remove upper phase and transfer to a new 1.5 mL tube","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

steps.section: DNA extraction Protocol (from cell growth to final DNA product):
steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"cmoo2","text":"31.  Add 6 volumes of ice cold isopropanol and mix by inverting","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

steps.section: DNA extraction Protocol (from cell growth to final DNA product):
steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"6dahe","text":"(PAUSE POINT) Place tubes in -20 °C freezer for 15 minutes OR OVERNIGHT/FOR MULTIPLE DAYS","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

steps.section: DNA extraction Protocol (from cell growth to final DNA product):
steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"84n0q","text":"Centrifuge tubes in 4 °C at 13,000x g for 20 mins","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

steps.section: DNA extraction Protocol (from cell growth to final DNA product):
steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"1su15","text":"Remove all liquid and let air dry for 30 mins to over night, until it’s dry to remove excess alcohol","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

steps.section: DNA extraction Protocol (from cell growth to final DNA product):
steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"182u2","text":"Resuspend pellet in 30-50 µL of UltraPure water or TE buffer ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

steps.section: DNA clean-up
steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"f65ab","text":"Add 0.1 volumes of 3M Sodium Acetate and 3 volumes of ice cold 100% Ethanol to your DNA samples, mix by inverting.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

steps.section: DNA clean-up
steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"6ue73","text":"Freeze samples at -80° C for 20mins or at -20° C overnight.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

steps.section: DNA clean-up
steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"40eq4","text":"Centrifuge tubes at 4° C at max speed for 30 minutes","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

steps.section: DNA clean-up
steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"eai11","text":"Remove supernatant and resuspend pellet in 1mL of ice cold 70% Ethanol, being sure the DNA pellet becomes loose from the tube and floats freely in the liquid.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

steps.section: DNA clean-up
steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"1nqji","text":"Centrifuge at 4° C  at max speed for 10 minutes","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

steps.section: DNA clean-up
steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"6gs87","text":"Remove Ethanol and let tubes dry completely with no ethanol left in the tubes. Overnight with running air over the open tubes works best.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

steps.section: DNA clean-up
steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"1ijk1","text":"Pre-heat elution buffer (TE or water) at 65° C, then re-suspend DNA in 30-50µL of warmed elution buffer","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

steps.section: Preparing Yeast from liquid culture for DNA extraction
steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"arobu","text":"Place tube of cell pellet in liquid nitrogen to freeze cells, then keep tube in -80 freezer until you are ready to perform the DNA extraction.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

steps.section: Preparing Yeast from solid culture for DNA extraction
steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"7j4d4","text":"Place tube in liquid nitrogen to flash freeze, and place frozen tube in -80 freezer until you are ready to do the DNA extraction","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

steps.section: DNA extraction Protocol (from cell growth to final DNA product):
steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"8jju4","text":"START OF DNA EXTRACTION","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
